data.name: ExclusiveOrConstraint.ClassName
data.comment: Text used as the class name, displayed in the properties window.

data.name: ExclusiveOrConstraint.ExclusionConstraintName.DisplayName
data.comment: Text used as the name for Name property of the coupled exclusion constraint, displayed in the properties window.

data.name: ExclusiveOrConstraint.MandatoryConstraintName.DisplayName
data.comment: Text used as the name for Name property of the coupled mandatory constraint, displayed in the properties window.

data.name: FactType.RemoveImpliedInternalUniquenessConstraints.TransactionName
data.comment: The name of the transaction that auto-fixes implied and duplicate internal constraints.

data.name: FrequencyConstraint.UnboundedMaxValueText
data.comment: Text used in the dropdown editor and type converter for the frequency constraint max value. Correspond to the 0 value in the object model.

data.name: ImplicitBooleanValueType.PropertyRestriction
data.value: The modification of the IsImplicitBooleanValue property on a ValueType is not allowed.
data.comment: Error message for when a user attempts to modify properties on an Implicit Boolean ValueType

data.name: ImplicitBooleanValueType.Restriction
data.value: The modification of properties on an Implicit Boolean ValueType is not allowed.
data.comment: Error message for when a user attempts to modify the IsImplicitBooleanValueType property on a ValueType

data.name: ImplicitBooleanValueType.NoReadingFormatString
data.comment: The format string for naming an implicit boolean value type when there are no readings on the fact type.

data.name: ImpliedFactType.PredicateInverseReading
data.comment: The inverse reading for the predicate created implicitly via objectification. There is no attempt made to keep the predicate readings unique in ring situations.We allow the model error to populate instead of generating an articial unique reading.

data.name: ImpliedFactType.PredicateReading
data.comment: The reading for the predicate created implicitly via objectification.There is no attempt made to keep the predicate readings unique in ring situations.We allow the model error to populate instead of generating an articial unique reading.

data.name: Model.Reading.RoleDeletedText
data.comment: Text used to replace a role place holder when the role is deleted

data.name: ModelContextWindow.WindowTitle
data.comment: Text to place in the title bar of the context tool window.

data.name: ModelError.Constraint.CompatibleRolePlayerTypeError.Set.Text
data.value: Constraint '{0}' in model '{1}' has role players with incompatible types.
data.comment: The role players in an external constraint must have compatible types. Replacement field {0} is the constraint name and {1} is the model name.

data.name: ModelError.Constraint.CompatibleRolePlayerTypeError.SetComparison.Text
data.value: Constraint '{0}' in model '{1}' has role players in column '{2}' with incompatible types.
data.comment: The role players in an external constraint column must have compatible types. Replacement field {0} is the constraint name, {1} is the model name, and {2} is the (1-based) column number.

data.name: ModelError.Constraint.ContradictionError.Text
data.value: Constraints {0} in model '{1}' are in a state of contradiction.
data.comment: Model validation error text when a constraint intersects a second constraint where the second constraints roles are a subset of the constraint roles and are in a state of contradiction.

data.name: ModelError.Constraint.EqualityOrSubsetImpliedByMandatoryError.Text
data.value: Constraint '{0}' in model '{1}' is implied by intersecting simple mandatory constraints.
data.comment: Model validation error text when an equality or subset constraint is put on roles that are mandatory.

data.name: ModelError.Constraint.ExternalConstraintArityMismatch.Text
data.value: Constraint '{0}' has role sequences with different numbers of roles.
data.comment: Model validation error text when role sequences in a multi column constraint have different role counts (arity).

data.name: ModelError.Constraint.ExternalEqualityImpliedByMandatory.Text
data.value: Constraint '{0}' in Model '{1}' is implied by mandatory constraint(s).
data.comment: Model validation error text when two roles played by the same object have an external equality constrant and also have both roles identified as mandatory. {0}=constraint name {1}=model name

data.name: ModelError.Constraint.FrequencyConstraintContradictsInternalUniquenessConstraintError.Text
data.value: Frequency constraint '{0}' in model '{2}' contradicts one or more internal uniqueness constraints on FactType '{1}'.
data.comment: Model validation error text used when a frequency constraint contradicts an internal uniqueness constraint

data.name: ModelError.Constraint.FrequencyConstraintMinMaxError.Text
data.value: Maximum value for constraint '{0}' in model '{1}' cannot be less than the minimum value.
data.comment: The frequency constraint minimum must be less than or equal to the maximum. {0}=constraint name {1}=model name

data.name: ModelError.Constraint.ImplicationError.Text
data.value: Constraint '{0}' in model '{1}' is implied by at least one constraint of the same type attached to a subset of the same roles.
data.comment: Model validation error text when a constraint intersects a second constraint where the second constraints roles are a subset of the constraint roles.

data.name: ModelError.Constraint.NotWellModeledSubsetAndMandatoryError.Text
data.value: Subset constraint '{0}' and mandatory constraint '{1}' in model '{2}' are not well-modeled. Suggested ways to fix: (1) Delete the mandatory constraint. (2) Add another mandatory constraint on the superset role. (3) Delete the subset constraint.
data.comment: Model validation error text when a mandatory constraint is put on the subset role of a subset constraint relationship.

data.name: ModelError.Constraint.RingConstraintTypeNotSpecifiedError.Message
data.value: The ring type for ring constraint '{0}' in model '{1}' is not specified.
data.comment: The ring constraint type must be specified. {0} is the constraint name and {1} is the model name.

data.name: ModelError.Constraint.TooFewRoleSequences.Text
data.value: Constraint '{0}' does not have enough role sequences.
data.comment: Model validation error text when too few role sequences are specified for a constraint. This is a common condition when constraints are being created.

data.name: ModelError.Constraint.TooManyRoleSequences.Text
data.value: Constraint '{0}' has too many role sequences.
data.comment: Model validation error text when too many role sequences are specified for a constraint. This is an uncommon condition that should only occur with a hand edit to a model file.

data.name: ModelError.EntityType.RequiresReferenceScheme.Message
data.value: Entity type '{0}' in model '{1}' requires a preferred reference scheme.
data.comment: An entity type must have a preferred reference scheme. Replacement field {0} is the entity type name and {1} is the model name.

data.name: ModelError.EntityTypeInstance.TooFewEntityTypeRoleInstances.Message
data.value: Entity type '{0}' in model '{1}' is missing instance data to completely identify a sample instance.
data.comment: Text displayed when there aren't enough entity type role instances to completely fill a single entity population row. {0}=entitytype, {1}=model.

data.name: ModelError.FactType.ImpliedInternalUniquenessConstraintError.Text
data.value: FactType '{0}' in model '{1}' contains one or more internal uniqueness constraints that are implied by or duplicates of other internal uniqueness constraints.
data.comment: Text used in the ImpliedInternalUniquenessConstraintError' {0}=fact type name {2}=model name

data.name: ModelError.FactType.NMinusOneRule.Text
data.value: Uniqueness constraint '{0}' on FactType '{1}' in model '{2}' must span at least {3} roles.
data.comment: Text diplayed in the Model Error when the span of the internal constraint is less than the span of the Fact Type - 1. {0}=constraint name, {1}=fact name, {2}=model name, {3}=factarity-1

data.name: ModelError.FactType.RequiresInternalUniquenessConstraint.Message
data.value: FactType '{0}' in model '{1}' requires an internal uniqueness constraint with alethic modality.
data.comment: Text displayed in the text of the FactTypeRequiresInternalUniquenessContraintError

data.name: ModelError.FactType.RequiresReading.Message
data.value: At least one reading is required for FactType '{0}' in model '{1}'.
data.comment: Text displayed in the text of the FactTypeRequiresReadingError

data.name: ModelError.FactTypeInstance.TooFewFactTypeRoleInstances.Message
data.value: FactType '{0}' in model '{1}' is missing instance data to completely identify a sample instance.
data.comment: Text displayed when there aren't enough fact type role instances to completely fill a single fact type population row. {0}=facttype {1}=model.

data.name: ModelError.Model.DuplicateConstraintNames.Text
data.value: Model '{0}' contains multiple constraints named '{1}'. Constraint names must be unique in the model.
data.comment: Model validation error text used when multiple constraints with the same name are loaded into a model. Field 0 is the model name, field 1 is the element name.This is an uncommon condition that should only occur with a hand edit to a model file.

data.name: ModelError.Model.DuplicateObjectTypeNames.Text
data.value: Model '{0}' contains multiple object types named '{1}'. Type names must be unique across all entity and value types in a model.
data.comment: Model validation error text used when multiple object types with the same name are loaded into a model.Field 0 is the model name, field 1 is the element name.This is an uncommon condition that should only occur with a hand edit to a model file.

data.name: ModelError.Model.PopulationMandatoryError.Text
data.value: '{0}' instance '{1}' in model '{2}' must participate in FactType '{3}'{4}.
data.comment: Model validation error shown when a population violates a mandatory constraint. Field 0 is the name of the role player, field 1 is the derived name of the instance, field 2 is the model name, field 3 is the name of the first facttype name, field 4 is a placeholder for additional fact types.

data.name: ModelError.Model.PopulationMandatoryError.AdditionalFactTypeText
data.comment: Model validation error shown when a population violates a mandatory constraint (additional fact types). Field 0 is the name of the fact type, field 1 is the following fact type (replaced by yet another trailing fact type, if available).

data.name: ModelError.Model.PopulationUniquenessError.FactType.Text
data.value: '{0}' instance '{1}' in model '{2}' violates a uniqueness constraint on FactType '{3}'.
data.comment: Model validation error shown when a population violates a uniqueness constraint and its role is unnamed. Field 0 is the name of the object type, field 1 is the string representation of the instance, field 2 is the model name, field 3 is the facttype name.

data.name: ModelError.Model.PopulationUniquenessError.Role.Text
data.value: '{0}' instance '{1}' in model '{2}' violates a uniqueness constraint for Role '{3}'.
data.comment: Model validation error shown when a population violates a uniqueness constraint and its role is named. Field 0 is the name of the object type, field 1 is the string representation of the instance, field 2 is the model name, field 3 is the role name.

data.name: ModelError.ObjectType.CompatibleSupertypesError.Message
data.value: Direct supertypes of ObjectType '{0}' in model '{1}' must be overlapping without transitive implication.
data.comment: Text displayed in the text of the CompatibleSupertypesError. {0}=ObjectType name {1}=model name.

data.name: ModelError.ObjectType.ObjectTypeRequiresPrimarySupertypeError.Message
data.value: Object type '{0}' in model '{1}' requires a primary supertype.
data.comment: Text displayed in the text of the ObjectTypeRequiresPrimarySupertypeError. {0}=ObjectType name {1}=model name

data.name: ModelError.ObjectType.PreferredIdentifierRequiresMandatoryError.Message
data.value: Object type '{0}' in model '{1}' has a preferred identification scheme with no corresponding mandatory roles. One or more near roles in the facts attached to the preferred identifier must be mandatory.
data.comment: Text displayed in the text of the PreferredIdentifierRequiresMandatoryError. {0}=ObjectType name {1}=model name

data.name: ModelError.Reading.RequiresUserModification.Message
data.value: FactType '{0}' in model '{1}' requires user modification of the reading text '{2}'.
data.comment: Text displayed in the text of the ReadingRequiresUserModificationError. {0}=fact name,{1}=model name,{2}=reading text

data.name: ModelError.Reading.TooFewRoles.Message
data.value: FactType '{0}' in model '{1}' has too few roles for the reading with text '{2}'.
data.comment: Text displayed in the text of the TooFewRolesError. {0}=fact name,{1}=model name,{2}=reading text

data.name: ModelError.Reading.TooManyRoles.Message
data.value: FactType '{0}' in model '{1}' has too many roles for the reading with text '{2}'.
data.comment: Text displayed in the text of the TooManyRolesError. {0}=fact name,{1}=model name,{2}=reading text

data.name: ModelError.Role.RolePlayerRequired.Message
data.value: Role '{0}' in FactType '{1}' in model '{2}' requires a role player.
data.comment: Text displayed in the text of the RoleRequiresRolePlayerError. {0} is the (1-based) role number, {1} is the name of the fact, and {2} is the name of the model.

data.name: ModelError.UncategorizedModelError.CategoryDisplayName
data.comment: Category name to display for uncategorized model errors.

data.name: ModelError.ValueConstraint.ValueRangeOverlapError.Role.Message
data.value: Role '{2}' of FactType '{1}' in model '{0}' has a value constraint with overlapping values.
data.comment: ValueRangeOverlapError text for a RoleValueConstraint. {0}=model {1}=facttype {2}=role number.

data.name: ModelError.ValueConstraint.ValueRangeOverlapError.ValueType.Message
data.value: The value constraint for '{0}' in model '{1}' has overlapping values.
data.comment: ValueRangeOverlapError text for a ValueTypeConstraint. {0}=valuetype {1}=model.

data.name: ModelError.ValueRange.MaxValueMismatchError.Role.Message
data.value: Role '{2}' of FactType '{1}' in model '{0}' has a max value that does not match the specified data type.
data.comment: Role data type does not match max inclusion. {0}=model {1}=facttype {2}=role number.

data.name: ModelError.ValueRange.MaxValueMismatchError.ValueType.Message
data.value: The max value for '{0}' in model '{1}' must match the specified data type.
data.comment: data type does not match max inclusion. {0}=valuetype {1}=model.

data.name: ModelError.ValueRange.MinValueMismatchError.Role.Message
data.value: Role '{2}' of FactType '{1}' in model '{0}' has a min value that does not match the specified data type.
data.comment: Role data type does not match min inclusion. {0}=model {1}=facttype {2}=role number.

data.name: ModelError.ValueRange.MinValueMismatchError.ValueType.Message
data.value: The min value for '{0}' in model '{1}' must match the specified data type.
data.comment: data type does not match min inclusion. {0}=valuetype {1}=model.

data.name: ModelError.ValueType.DataTypeNotSpecified.Message
data.value: A data type must be specified for value type '{0}' in model '{1}'.
data.comment: Text displayed for an unspecified data type

data.name: ModelError.ValueTypeInstance.CompatibleValueTypeInstanceValue.Message
data.value: Value '{0}' in the sample population for value type '{1}' in model '{2}' is not of the specified data type '{3}'.
data.comment: Text displayed when the data type of the sample data doesn't match it's set data type. {0}=value {1}=valuetype {2}=model.

data.name: ModelErrorDisplayFilter.ToStringOverrideText
data.comment: Text to display for the property for the ModelErrorDisplayFilter when it is filtered.

data.name: ModelException.Constraint.EnforceNoForeignFactTypes
data.value: A constraint must be attached to a fact type in the same model as the constraint.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to attached facts from an external model to a constraint.

data.name: ModelException.Constraint.EnforceSingleFactTypeForInternalConstraint
data.value: Internal constraint can only have one associated fact. The IsInternal property must be cleared before adding roles from a second fact type to the constraint.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to attached more than one fact type to an internal constraint.

data.name: ModelException.ConstraintRoleSequenceHasRole.EnforceNoRolePlayerChange
data.value: Direct modification of role players on a ConstraintRoleSequenceHasRole relationship is not supported. As an alternative, first delete the link then add a new one.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to directly modify role players on the ConstraintRoleSequenceHasRole relationship.

data.name: ModelException.EntityTypeInstance.InvalidEntityTypeParent
data.value: Sample entity instances can only be hooked up to an entity.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to hook up a ValueType to an EntityTypeInstance.

data.name: ModelException.EntityTypeInstance.InvalidRolesPreferredIdentifier
data.value: All sample value roles must be part of the parent entity type's preferred identifier.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to hook up role instances to an entity type where the roles are not in the entity type's preferred identifier collection.

data.name: ModelException.ExclusiveOrConstraintCoupler.DirectExclusionConstraintEdit
data.value: Roles on an ExclusionConstraint linked to a MandatoryConstraint with an ExclusiveOrCoupler should be edited indirectly via the MandatoryConstraint.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to directly edit roles on an ExclusionConstraint that participates in an ExclusiveOrCoupler relationship.

data.name: ModelException.ExclusiveOrConstraintCoupler.InconsistentConstraintRolesOrModality
data.value: An ExclusiveOr coupling between a MandatoryConstraint and ExclusionConstraint requires a single-column exclusion constraint with the same roles and modality as the MandatoryConstraint.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to form an ExclusiveOrConstraintCoupler relationship between incompatible MandatoryConstraint and ExclusionConstraint elements.

data.name: ModelException.Fact.AddReading.InvalidReadingText
data.value: Reading text is not in a valid format.
data.comment: The error message that is returned when attempting to add a new reading to a fact type and the text is not valid. Validate reading text must have the number of placeholders equal to the number of roles in the FactType. The replacement fields must be ordered and identified using String.Format replacement syntax. For example: "{0} has {1}".

data.name: ModelException.FactType.EnforceNoImplicitBooleanValueTypeRolePlayerChange
data.value: The role associated with an implicit boolean value type cannot be changed.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to modify a role player associated with an implicit boolean value.

data.name: ModelException.FactType.EnforceNoRoleMigration
data.value: A Role must remain with the FactType it was originally associated with.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to move a role to a different FactType.

data.name: ModelException.FactType.EnforceRolePlayerNotNestingType
data.value: A role player cannot be the type objectifying the role's parent fact type.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to use the same type as both a role player and the nesting type of a fact type.

data.name: ModelException.FactTypeInstance.InconsistentRoleOwners
data.value: All roles in a fact type instance must be owned by the same fact type.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to add roles from different fact types to a role sequence owned by a fact type instance.

data.name: ModelException.Model.DuplicateName.Text
data.value: The name '{0}' is already in use in this model.
data.comment: Exception message when a name change in the editor attempts to introduce a duplicate name into the model.

data.name: ModelException.ModelErrorCategory.TypeNotDerivedFromModelErrorCategory
data.value: The type specified for the ModelErrorDisplayFilterAttribute must be derived from ModelErrorCategory.
data.comment: Exception message when a ModelErrorDisplayFilterAttribute is initialized with a type that does not derive from ModelErrorCategory.

data.name: ModelException.Objectification.DirectModificationOfImpliedElement
data.value: Facts and constraints implied by an Objectification relationship cannot be directly modified.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to modify roles, constraints, and role players on elements implied by an Objectification relationship.

data.name: ModelException.Objectification.ImpliedFactTypesCannotBeObjectified
data.value: A FactType that is implied by an Objectification cannot be objectified.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to objectify a fact type that is implied by another objectification.

data.name: ModelException.Objectification.ImpliedMustBeImpliedAndIndependentAndCannotPlayRoleInNonImpliedFact
data.value: Implied objectifications must be implied, must be independent (if possible), and must only play roles in implied fact types.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to change an explicit Objectification to implied when it does not match the implied objectification pattern or is not independent (if possible) or plays a Role in a non-implied FactType.

data.name: ModelException.Objectification.ImpliedObjectificationNotAllowed
data.value: Implied objectifications can not be operated on via this method.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to operate on an implied objectification by a method that only accepts explicit objectifications.

data.name: ModelException.ObjectType.EnforceIsIndependentPattern
data.value: IsIndependent can only be true on an ObjectType that only participates in mandatory roles relating to its preferred identifier.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to set the IsIndependent property on an object type that plays mandatory roles that are not part of its preferred identification scheme.

data.name: ModelException.ObjectType.EnforcePreferredIdentifierForEntityType
data.value: An object type with a preferred identifier must be an entity type.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to set both a primary identifier and a value type on the same object type.

data.name: ModelException.ObjectType.EnforceValueTypeNotNestingType
data.value: An object type cannot be both a value type and an objectified fact type.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to make an object type both a value type and an objectified fact type.

data.name: ModelException.Reading.IsPrimary.ReadOnlyWhenFalse
data.value: The IsPrimaryForReadingOrder and IsPrimaryForFactType properties cannot be set to false, set it to true for the new primary reading and this will occur automatically
data.comment: Exception message output when an attempt is made to set the IsPrimaryForReadingOrder or IsPrimaryForFactType properties of a Reading to false.

data.name: ModelException.ReferenceMode.AmbiguousName
data.value: Multiple reference modes found with the same name. Use the reference mode picker instead of setting the name directly.
data.comment: Exception message output when multiple reference modes are found with the same name

data.name: ModelException.ReferenceMode.EnforceUniqueFormatString
data.value: Format strings must be unique across all reference modes in the model.
data.comment: Exception message when the unique format string rule is violated for reference modes

data.name: ModelException.ReferenceMode.IntrinsicRefModesDontChange
data.value: Reference mode kind cannot be changed for intrinsic reference modes.
data.comment: Exception messege when atttempt is made to change the kind of an intrinsic reference mode

data.name: ModelException.ReferenceMode.ReferenceModesKindNotEmpty
data.value: Reference mode kind cannot be empty.
data.comment: Exception message when attempt is made to remove reference mode kind.

data.name: ModelException.ReferenceModeKind.EnforceUniqueFormatString
data.value: Format strings must be unique across all reference mode kinds in the model.
data.comment: Exception message when the unique format string rule is violated for reference mode kinds

data.name: ModelException.Role.IsMandatoryRequiresAttachedFactType
data.value: A Role must be owned by a FactType to set the IsMandatory property.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to set the IsMandatory property on an unattached role. IsMandatory creates an internal constraint, which is owned by an FactType, so cannot be realized if the parent FactType is unknown.

data.name: ModelException.SubtypeFact.ConstraintAndRolePatternFixed
data.value: The role and constraint patterns of a subtype relationship cannot be modified.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to modify the roles collection or internal constraints of a SubtypeFact.

data.name: ModelException.SubtypeFact.Cycle
data.value: A cycle has been detected in a chain of subtype relationships. A subtype must not be the direct or indirect subtype of its supertype.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to add a subtype relationship where the subtype is a direct or indirect subtype of the supertype.

data.name: ModelException.SubtypeFact.MetaRolesMustBeUsedOnSubtypeFact
data.value: The SubtypeMetaRole and SupertypeMetaRole can only be used with a SubtypeFact.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to attach SubtypeMetaRole or SuperTypeMetaRole objects to a FactType that is not a SubtypeFact.

data.name: ModelException.SubtypeFact.NotNested
data.value: A SubtypeFact cannot be a nested fact type
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to nest a SubtypeFact.

data.name: ModelException.SubtypeFact.PrimaryMustBeTrue
data.value: The SubtypeFact.IsPrimary property cannot be set to false.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to change the SubtypeFact.IsPrimary property to false.

data.name: ModelException.SubtypeFact.RolePlayersTypesNotMixed
data.value: The Subtype and Supertype ObjectTypes of a SubtypeFact must either be EntityTypes or ValueTypes, not one of each.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to mix EntityType and ValueType role players on a SubtypeFact.

data.name: ModelException.SubtypeMetaRole.OnlyAllowsImplicitConstraints
data.value: A SubtypeMetaRole cannot only be constrained by implicit single-role uniqueness and mandatory constraints.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to constraint a SubtypeMetaRole with a constraint other than the implicit uniqueness and mandatory constraints.

data.name: ModelException.SupertypeMetaRole.DisjunctiveMandatoryMustContainOnlySupertypeMetaRoles
data.value: A DisjunctiveMandatory constraint on a SubtypeFact must constrain only SubtypeFacts.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to mix Roles and SupertypeMetaRoles in the same DisjunctiveMandatory constraint.

data.name: ModelException.SupertypeMetaRole.ExclusionMustBeSingleColumnAndContainOnlySupertypeMetaRoles
data.value: An Exclusion constraint on a SubtypeFact must have a single column and constrain only SubtypeFacts.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to mix Roles and SupertypeMetaRoles in the same Exclusion constraint or to constraint SubtypeFacts with a multi-column Exclusion constraint.

data.name: ModelException.SupertypeMetaRole.OnlyAllowsImplicitDisjunctiveMandatoryAndExclusionConstraints
data.value: A SupertypeMetaRole can only be constrained by an implicit single-role uniqueness constraint and single-column Exclusion or DisjunctiveMandatory constraints.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to constraint a SupertypeMetaRole with a constraint other than the implicit uniqueness constraint, or disjunctive mandatory or exclusion constraints.

data.name: ModelException.UniquenessConstraint.InvalidPreferredIdentifierPreConditions
data.value: The current state of the roles attached to the external uniqueness constraint do no permit its use as a preferred identifier. All roles must be on a binary fact types, and all opposite roles must be attached to the same non-ValueType ObjectType. All opposite roles must also have single-column uniqueness constraints, but this precondition is applied automatically by the object model if it is not satisfied.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to set a uniqueness constraint as a preferred identifier when the preconditions are not met.

data.name: ModelException.ValueTypeInstance.InvalidValueTypeParent
data.value: Sample value instances can only be hooked up to a value type.
data.comment: Exception message when an attempt is made to hook up an EntityType to a ValueTypeInstance.

data.name: ModelNotesWindow.RootTypeNameNotesSeparatorFormatString
data.comment: Text that separates a root type's name from notes if multiple notes are displayed in the ORM notes window. Replacement field 0 is the element name, 1 is the note text.

data.name: ModelDefinitionWindow.WindowTitle
data.comment: Text to place in the title bar of the description editor tool window.

data.name: ModelNotesWindow.WindowTitle
data.comment: Text to place in the title bar of the notes editor tool window.

data.name: ModelReadingEditor.AllReadingsNodeName
data.comment: Text to use for the display All readings node in the readings editor tool window.

data.name: ModelReadingEditor.ChangePrimaryReadingText
data.comment: Text used to label the transaction created when the primary reading is changed through the reading editor.

data.name: ModelReadingEditor.ChangeReadingText
data.comment: Text used to describe the transaction created when the text of a reading is changed through the editor.

data.name: ModelReadingEditor.ImpliedFactTypeReadingsText
data.comment: Text used as the header row for the implied readings in the reading editor for a role selection on an objectified fact type.

data.name: ModelReadingEditor.IsPrimaryToolTip
data.value: Indicates if the Reading is the primary one for the ReadingOrder that it belongs to.
data.comment: Text used for the ToolTip on the IsPrimary column of the reading list.

data.name: ModelReadingEditor.ListColumnHeader.IsPrimary
data.comment: Text used for IsPrimary column header in the reading editor tool window.

data.name: ModelReadingEditor.ListColumnHeader.ReadingText
data.comment: The text that will be displayed in the column header of the reading list in the reading editor tool window.

data.name: ModelReadingEditor.MissingRolePlayerText
data.comment: Text to display in the reading editor when the role has no roleplayer to substitute into the text.

data.name: ModelReadingEditor.MoveReading
data.comment: Text used to label the transaction created when a reading is moved through the reading editor.

data.name: ModelReadingEditor.MoveReadingOrder
data.comment: Text used to label the transaction created when a reading order is moved through the reading editor.

data.name: ModelReadingEditor.NewItemText
data.comment: Text to place in the new item entry of the readings list in the reading editor tool window

data.name: ModelReadingEditor.NewReadingTransactionText
data.comment: Text used to describe the transaction created when creating a new reading.

data.name: ModelReadingEditor.PrimaryFactTypeReadingsText
data.comment: Text used as the header row for the primary readings in the reading editor for a role selection on an objectified fact type.

data.name: ModelReadingEditor.UnsupportedSelectionText
data.value: Select an item related to a FactType
data.comment: Text to place in the reading editor when the document view currently has a selection with no associated reading.

data.name: ModelReadingEditor.WindowTitle
data.comment: Text to place in the title of the reading editor tool window.

data.name: ModelReferenceModeEditor.AbbreviatedEntityTypeName
data.comment: Abbreviated form of the entity type name

data.name: ModelReferenceModeEditor.AbbreviatedReferenceModeName
data.comment: Abbreviated form of the reference mode name
